se.sics.tasim.props

Class RFQBundle

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.sics.tasim.props.RFQBundle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Transportable

    public class RFQBundle
extends java.lang.Object
implements Transportable, java.io.Serializable
    RFQBundle contains an ordered set of requests for quotes. Each request for quote (RFQ) contains:
    • RFQ id - a, for the sender, unique id for this RFQ
    • Product id - the requested product
    • Quantity - the requested quantity of products
    • Due date - the latest delivery date
    • Penalty - the penalty for late delivery of the order (optional)
    • Reserve price per unit - the reserve price for each unit (optional)

    Warning: serialized objects of this class might not be compatible with future versions. Only use serialization of this class for temporary storage or RMI using the same version of the class.

        rfqID - the id of the RFQ
        productID - the requested component
        quantity - the requested quantity
        reservePricePerUnit - the reservation price or 0 for no price constraints

      • getPenalty

        public int getPenalty(int index)
        Returns the penalty for late deliveries of the specified RFQ. The penalty is specified as the total sum that is charged on late deliveries. Usually the penalty is charged day for day until the delivery has been made or the order been voided.
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the RFQ in this bundle
        Returns:
        the penalty for late deliveries or 0 for no penalty

      • getReservePricePerUnit

        public int getReservePricePerUnit(int index)
        Returns the reserve price per unit for the specified RFQ. This is the maximal price the sender of the request is willing to pay per unit in the order.

        This is optional information that the sender might supply.

        Parameters:
        index - the index of the RFQ in this bundle
        Returns:
        the reserve price per unit or 0 if no reserve price has been specified by the sender
